Title: Chattahoochee
Album: A Lot About Livin' (And A Little 'Bout Love)
Comment: A 1993 all-timer from Alan Jackson (no relation), “Chattahoochee” showcases the prominent pedal steel and smooth neotraditional production that Jackson, George Strait & others held fast to even as pop and rock influences became increasingly commonplace in mainstream country. Jackson’s 1994 “Gone Country” explicitly describes the opportunists flooding Nashville for a piece of the country market and arguably fits the theme better, but “Chattahoochee” goes way harder, so fuck it.
